HEADWORD: Cryptocrystalline
<hw>Cryp`to*crys"tal*line</hw> <pr>(-kr?s"t<it>a</it>l-l?n)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>krypto`s</grk> hidden + E.
<ets>crystalline</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Indistinctly
crystalline; -- applied to rocks and minerals, whose state of
aggregation is so fine that no distinct particles are visible, even
under the microscope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

